4710719610a5\" data-recommend-id=\"image://fa20fb36f7232c1976e24710719610a5\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"The protagonist of Slitterhead atacks a monster while Steam user reviews float around them.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eCreated by the same talent behind the \u003cem\u003eSilent Hill\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003eSiren \u003c/em\u003eseries, \u003cem\u003eSlitterhead \u003c/em\u003ewas already positioned to perform well within the horror gaming community. With a unique premise, including possession and body horror, along with a vibrant city full of glowing neon lights illuminating the ever-present darkness, the third-person action-oriented horror game stood a great chance at making waves. Despite the studio’s reputation and history, they remained an indie outfit, which likely explains the game’s somewhat soft, understated reception.  - Brandon Morgan \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/slitterhead-as-told-by-steam-reviews-1851708414?_gl=1*1bl4u8j*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc4MzcyLjYwLjAuMA..\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/slitterhead-as-told-by-steam-reviews-1851708414?_gl=1*1bl4u8j*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc4MzcyLjYwLjAuMA..\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a\" data-recommend-id=\"image://443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Art from Nine Sols, Mouthwashing, and Zelda.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"Art from Nine Sols, Mouthwashing, and Zelda.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Art from Nine Sols, Mouthwashing, and Zelda.\" data-chomp-id=\"443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Art from Nine Sols, Mouthwashing, and Zelda.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: RedCandleGames / Wrong Organ / Nintendo / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a\" data-recommend-id=\"image://443cb764ae416bbc8eeed5ccc3c2490a\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Art from Nine Sols, Mouthwashing, and Zelda.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s the Thanksgiving holiday week, and that means if you work for a company worth a damn (and some that aren’t worth a damn, but I digress), you probably have the next couple of days off. (Apologies to anyone who works retail.) You might be buying some games you missed this year during Black Friday sales, or perhaps you’re completely at a loss for what to play. Fear not, my friend. We’re here to suggest some games to get you through the long weekend, and all the nonsense your hometown will put you through while you’re there. - Kenneth Shepard \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/kotaku-weekend-guide-zelda-robocop-mouthwashing-1851709672?_gl=1*1bl4u8j*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc4MzcyLjYwLjAuMA..\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/kotaku-weekend-guide-zelda-robocop-mouthwashing-1851709672?_gl=1*1bl4u8j*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczMjk3NTgzMS4zOTcuMS4xNzMyOTc4MzcyLjYwLjAuMA..\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a scenic view of the Poppy Field anomaly in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a scenic view of the Poppy Field anomaly in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A screenshot shows a scenic view of the Poppy Field anomaly in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl.\" data-chomp-id=\"e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a scenic view of the Poppy Field anomaly in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: GSC Game World / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e389535a7ab2d0338f6c1d215fd580e2\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a scenic view of the Poppy Field anomaly in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eUpon completing the game’s prologue and finally stepping foot into the Zone proper, you’ll head for Zalissya, this game’s version of the rookie town. There, you’ll encounter a handful of characters who will help propel the story forward, along with merchants, technicians, and even your first up close and personal interaction with a faction. You’ll also need money—well, coupons in this universe. You’ll find Mityay arguing with another Stalker in the merchant’s shop, and if you choose to accept his quest, he’ll send you to a dangerous anomaly field known as the Poppy Field. It’s gorgeous and deadly in equal measures. - Brandon Morgan \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/stalker-2-poppy-field-coupons-location-pomor-1851707719\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/stalker-2-poppy-field-coupons-location-pomor-1851707719\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a first-person view of the AR416 assault rifle in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a first-person view of the AR416 assault rifle in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A screenshot shows a first-person view of the AR416 assault rifle in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl\" data-chomp-id=\"b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a first-person view of the AR416 assault rifle in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: GSC Game World / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187\" data-recommend-id=\"image://b4541b8b7eb7a6d350d72fd2850a9187\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A screenshot shows a first-person view of the AR416 assault rifle in Stalker 2: Heart of Chornobyl\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt happens to the best of us: You’re delving into a dank, decrepit bunker in the post-apocalypse searching for rare loot, casually popping off shots at the various rat-like mutants scurrying through the dark when your weapon jams. In a moment of panic, you attempt to reload and clear the jam, but your weapon is so degraded it’s unusable. What now? In \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;External link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://humblebundleinc.sjv.io/c/379647/2059850/25796?subId1=KT-\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humblebundle.com%2Fstore%2Fstalker-2-heart-of-chornobyl%3Fhmb_source%3Dsearch_bar\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://humblebundleinc.sjv.io/c/379647/2059850/25796?subId1=KT-\u0026amp;u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.humblebundle.com%2Fstore%2Fstalker-2-heart-of-chornobyl%3Fhmb_source%3Dsearch_bar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eS.T.A.L.K.E.R. 2\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e, these situations occur rapidly and frequently, making the series’ signature dangerous environment more harsh than ever. Thanks,realism.  - Brandon Morgan \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/stalker-2-weapon-upgrade-attachment-repair-broken-1851707644\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/stalker-2-weapon-upgrade-attachment-repair-broken-1851707644\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
